lation on small scales appears to be difficult, while the void recovery rate improves significantly on scales {\textgreater}3h-1Mpc. A study of small-scale voids and the void galaxy population should therefore be restricted to the local Universe, out to at most 100h-1Mpc. {\textcopyright} 2011 The Authors Monthly Notices of the Royal Astronomical Society {\textcopyright} 2011 RAS.},
archivePrefix = {arXiv},
arxivId = {1107.1488},
author = {Platen, Erwin and {Van de Weygaert}, Rien and Jones, Bernard J.T. and Vegter, Gert and Calvo, Miguel A.Arag{\'{o}}n},
doi = {10.1111/j.1365-2966.2011.18905.x},
eprint = {1107.1488},
